commit.message: 0.1.6 rc2; update changelogs, etc.
fix: add .bats and .txt under tests/, and .txt
fix: make unused-imports ignored by py flake8
fix: disable coverage tests until fixing errors by cheetah generated code
fix: cleanup travis-ci configuration

fix/change: cleanup and add various tests

- tox.ini: drop py3{4,5} and add py38 as test targets, add travis-ci
  configuration, follow changes in requiremnts.txt files, detect test
  target .py files dynamically, add min, releng and dists targets
- tests/releng.bats: add release engineering tests

fix/change: migrate requirements.txt using conditional requirements

- requirements.txt: relocate and migrate py2 requirements using
  conditional requirements described in PEP 508 and PEP 0345
- tests/requirements.txt: relocate and remove version restrictions
- pkg/requirements-py-2.7.txt: migrate into requirements.txt and
  tests/requirements.txt using conditional requirements
- pkg/test_requirements-py-2.7.txt: removed

fix/change: drop py2 support in RPMs and cleanup/fix packaging stuff

- setup.py: simplify the version detection code, revision support in the
  RELEASE tag in the RPM SPEC, remove unused import (sys).
- setup.cfg: add project_urls metadata to be shown in the PyPI page,
  drop python 3.3 .. 3.5 and add python 3.8 support, add minimum install
  dependencies, remove unsed pytest stuff
- pkg/package.spec.in: use Release tag instead of Version tag for
  snapshot versioning mode, drop py2 support and related hacks
change: renmae
fix: update the hacking (test) section
change: run flake8 directly instead of module
change: remove deprecated and unused wrapper script to run tests
change: remove deprecated and unused wrapper script to build rpms
enhancement: add python 3.7 tests in travis-ci
fix: drop python 3.3 tests in travis-ci because tox does not support it
change: use tox-travis to simplify the tests matrix in travis-ci
change: run tox instead of pkg/runtest.sh in travis-ci

change: some more cleanups and enhancements of tox configuration

some more cleanups and enhancements of tox configuration:

- pylint: remove --exit-zero option and put '- ' at the head of the line
  run it to avoid avorting with non-zero exit code on errors
- nose: add coverage related options
- remove commented lines no more used

fix: check code style and lint before performing unit tests

Check code style and lint before performing unit tests just like
pkg/runtest.sh does.
fix: remove the comment does not help much
fix: remove tox's py27-pytest target as it does not work

change: switch to use nose instead of the wrapper script in tox

Switch to use nose instead of the wrapper script pkg/runtest.sh in tox
to make tests work in non unix platforms.
fix: tweak search paths of the CLI script

change: add parmeters to support 'test' command of setuptools

Added some parmeters to support 'test' command of setuptools into
setup.cfg to make 'python setup.py test' in the future.

change: move sources of this package into src/

Move sources of this package into src/ to avoid some issues during
tests/.  Along with that, changed to follow this relocation in the
manifest file, RPM SPEC template and a couple of package configurations.

.. seealso:: https://blog.ionelmc.ro/2014/05/25/python-packaging/#the-structure

fix: test code were not included in source distribution

Resolve the issue that test code under tests/ were not included in
source distribution reported by jayvdb as issue #7.
fix: correct runtime dependencies
fix: bump up the revision

change: fixes and cleanups of the RPM SPEC

- Switch build of python{2,3} RPMs exclusively depends on the distribution
- Add hack to install necessary files for RHEL 7/EPEL 7
